          </p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            Texas House Democrats
            <a
              style="
                text-decoration: none;
                border-bottom: 2px solid #4d3060;
                color: black;
              "
              href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-4-aug-25-spotlight-h1-1-fled-the-state?source=website"
              target="_blank"
              >fled the state</a
            >
            to block a vote on a Republican-drafted congressional map that could
            eliminate five Democratic US House seats. Dozens of Democrats fled
            to Illinois with the support of the Illinois governor, who provided
            logistical support, while others fled to Boston and Albany. In
            response, the Republican governor threatened to expel the Democrats
            from the Texas State House, calling them ‚Äúfelons.‚Äù
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            Democrats assert that the redistricting was racial gerrymandering
            aimed at diluting Black and Latino voters. Meanwhile, Republicans
            argue that their map is lawful and is being redrawn to give
            Republicans a better prospect of gaining more seats in Illinois, as
            Democrats currently hold 14 legislative seats compared to
            Republicans‚Äô three. If passed, it would help Republicans retain
            control of Congress ahead of the 2026 midterm elections.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            Texas‚Äôs attorney general labeled Democrats ‚Äúcowards‚Äù who should be
            arrested and brought back to the Capitol. Absentees could face
            $500/day fines under rules enacted two years after state Democrats
            left the state for three weeks to
            <a
              style="
                text-decoration: none;
                border-bottom: 2px solid #4d3060;
                color: black;
              "
              href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-4-aug-25-spotlight-h1-2-block-an-elections-bill?source=website"
